<section id="tenth-angelyoshito-asari" class="level3">
<h3>Tenth Angel/Yoshito Asari</h3>
<p><a href="http://forum.evageeks.org/viewtopic.php?p=437736#437736">http://forum.evageeks.org/viewtopic.php?p=437736#437736</a></p>
<p>The design was requested early on. For â€œPreludeâ€, considerable changes were made to the battle with the sixth angel, which became the core of the work. For â€œBreak,â€ the battle with the tenth angel was supposed to correspond to that [climactic battle with the sixth]. [â€¦] I wonder if [Anno] just wanted something concrete to be used, temporarily, as an impetus for creating the â€œgimmicks,â€ battles, and so on, for the new parts of the work. As a result, in â€œBreak,â€ major innovations were incorporated into every angel battle.</p>
<p>Up until now, with the exception of the TV seriesâ€™ third angel, the angel design requests that I have received have all been explained with reference to a â€œgimmickâ€ within the work (the fourth angel has beam-like whips for arms, the fourteenth angel has folded fabric-like â€œcuttersâ€ for arms, and so on). As far as the initial request for the new version of the strongest angel, I only remember the vague description: â€œSomething like [the fourteenth angel in the TV series] appears; in reality it is something completely different.â€ To begin with, I submitted an idea where [â€œBreakâ€™sâ€ tenth angel] appears looking like the fourteenth angel of the TV series, with [a pair of] â€œbelt-likeâ€ arms wrapped around its body. When it unwraps itself, its form completely changes. After that, it is completely different than the TV seriesâ€™ fourteenth angel, with a terrifying shape â€¦ when I drew the angel, that was what I had in mind.</p>
<p>I submitted the first draft, and completely forgot about it until the beginning of 2007, when a rough sketch<a href="#fn121" class="footnoteRef" id="fnref121"><sup>121</sup></a> from the director suddenly arrived, with the following written upon it: â€œLike something wound upon a reel.â€ â€œLike the upper parts of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/King%20Joe%20%28Ultra%20monster%29" title="Wikipedia: King Joe (Ultra monster)">King Joe</a>?â€ â€œSomething consumed by the angel emerges.â€ To begin with, I thought about something that would incorporate that â€œgimmick.â€ I submitted an idea where, concerning the â€œconsumptionâ€, it extends a proboscis, penetrates the Eva, and draws out its insides.</p>
<p>There were further changes after that [â€¦] In the fourth draft the â€œgimmickâ€ of the battle solidified, [?] and an idea was presented where the angel transformed from its â€œflutteringâ€ condition, rolling up into a solid pipe, or else changing into the form of a spear. There was a design change in accordance with that.</p>
<p>The change where the absorbed Eva protruded from the [angelâ€™s] body itself was also a directoral request. Along with the disappearance of the torso in the design, the â€œflutteringâ€ was changed to resemble the palm of a hand. [â€¦] it seemed like an image where the absorbed Eva was manipulated like a puppet. [?] At that time the challenge was putting into effect an idea where the form, or, should I say, the texture of the whole, suddenly changes. From <em>funyaan</em> to <em>shakiin</em> [â€œlimpâ€ to â€œfirmâ€?]; that was the verbal instruction given by the director.</p>
<p>As far as Ayanamiâ€™s absorption was concerned, the instructions came from the director as well. I myself thought about a design where the entire body didnâ€™t emerge, but you would have the torso without the arms, or an asymmetry where an arm emerges in place of a leg, or where the body parts â€œcrossâ€ one another. However, when I tried drawing it, it wasnâ€™t as good as I expected.</p>
<p>I tried drawing various things, and left the final decision to the director.</p>
