<li id="fn6"><p>â€œTo be honest, my first instinct was to translate ã€è‰¯ã„ã‚­ãƒ£ãƒ©ã€ asâ€real characterâ€œ, whereâ€good&quot; means â€œwell-developedâ€. So, â€œreal characterâ€ or â€œwell-developed characterâ€. On the other hand, the context seemed to suggest that maybe Tsurumaki was proposing softening Asukaâ€™s character so that the audience couldnâ€™t fail to become emotionally invested in her before the Unit-03 sequence. In the end, I felt unsure, so I just translated it literally. I think symbv would certainly understand the remark, but Iâ€™m not 100% sure what it meantâ€œ. <a href="http://forum.evageeks.org/viewtopic.php?p=461297#461297">http://forum.evageeks.org/viewtopic.php?p=461297#461297</a></p>
