<li id="fn7"><p><a href="http://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=Death%20Flag">Urban Dictionary</a> defines it as</p>
<blockquote>
<p>â€œAn instance where a character is subject to extreme danger foreshadowed with grim implications. Examples of death flagging:</p>
<ul>
<li>Unknowingly ticking off a unstable individual.</li>
<li>Wondering into a zone at the wrong time.</li>
<li>Taking on a dangerous deed with slim chances of success.</li>
<li>Short sighted approach to a ludicrous event.&quot;</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<p>The NSFW site <a href="http://danbooru.donmai.us/post/index?tags=death_flag">Danbooru</a> defines it as</p>
<blockquote>
<p>â€œ<em>(Shibou Furagu)</em> A sign to the audience that a character is going to die. A death flag is usually raised by such things as saying or doing something that can be seen as tempting fate, a character doing something that he or she has been warned (sometimes repeatedly) will lead to death, an unrequited relationship finally being requited, etc.â€</p>
</blockquote>
